## Week-one failure modes

**Drift from append-only.** Gemini will occasionally rewrite an incident record instead of appending. Revert with OneDrive version history, add a sentence to GEMINI.md naming the specific drift.

**Context amnesia mid-session.** After ~30 minutes, it may stop referencing context/. Periodically say "re-read context/communication-style.yaml before drafting this."

**Route confusion on new cases.** The five-type classification is the thing Gemini is most likely to get wrong early. If it routes a third-party-incident as a cyber-incident, correct it explicitly and note the distinguishing signal in GEMINI.md.

**Silent overwrites in inputs/.** If you drop two files with the same name from different sources, OneDrive will version them but Gemini may not notice. Name inputs descriptively on drop.

**.msg files.** Gemini CLI can't reliably parse Outlook .msg. Convert manually to .md with From/To/Date/Subject headers before dropping in inputs/.
